<subSubSection id="07AF96B5FFF8FFD6F52464FAFE67C9E8" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF8FFD6F52464FAFF1ECA4D" blockId="28.[111,648,1262,1699]" box="[113,213,1262,1288]" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF8FFD6F5246519FE62C96E" blockId="28.[111,648,1262,1699]" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F5246519FECECA6C" box="[113,261,1293,1319]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F5246519FECECA6C" box="[113,261,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">Ocotea nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the three 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F4976519FD99CA6C" box="[450,594,1293,1319]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F4976519FDCCCA6C" box="[450,519,1293,1319]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">Ocotea</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
with rather large leaves which have a raised reticulation on the upper leaf surface. 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F4C26559FD4ECA2D" box="[407,645,1356,1383]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cryptocaryoides">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F4C26559FD4ECA2D" box="[407,645,1356,1383]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">Ocotea cryptocaryoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has glabrous inflorescences and glabrous twigs (pubescent in 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F4586598FEB6CAEE" box="[269,381,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F4586598FEB6CAEE" box="[269,381,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">O. nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F4806598FDF5CAEE" box="[469,574,1420,1446]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cymosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F4806598FDF5CAEE" box="[469,574,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">O. cymosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a finer reticulation on the leaves. The cupules of 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F5BB65DFFEAACAAE" box="[238,353,1483,1509]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F5BB65DFFEAACAAE" box="[238,353,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">O. nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have sometimes three ribs on the outside and resemble in this the 6-ribbed cupules of 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F5B3661FFE69C96F" box="[230,418,1546,1573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cryptocaryoides">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F5B3661FFE69C96F" box="[230,418,1546,1573]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">O. cryptocaryoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4F0AC53EFFF8FFD6F5DD663EFE67C9E8" blockId="28.[111,648,1262,1699]" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">
The 
<typeStatus id="900E7B9CFFF8FFD6F5EF663FFF22C90E" box="[186,233,1579,1605]" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="88B5BEBDFFF8FFD6F444663EFE4FC90F" box="[273,388,1578,1604]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Ocotea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="28" pageNumber="263" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nervosa">
<emphasis id="7DC1192CFFF8FFD6F444663EFE4FC90F" box="[273,388,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">O. nervosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of a twig with leaves and detached fruits. The leaves of the 
<typeStatus id="900E7B9CFFF8FFD6F70F665EFD43C92F" box="[602,648,1610,1636]" pageId="28" pageNumber="263">type</typeStatus>
are large and oblong and do not quite match the other collections placed here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
